Bethany Everts'),(10562,1095,'_field_6','East High School'),(10563,1095,'_field_7','Junior '),(10564,1095,'_field_8','Marcus and Charlotte Everts'),(10565,1095,'_field_9','3010 South 74th St'),(10566,1095,'_field_10','(402) 613-5742'),(10567,1095,'_field_11','bethanyeverts@yahoo.com'),(10568,1095,'_field_13','(402) 613-9227'),(10569,1095,'_field_15','ceverts@lps.org'),(10570,1095,'_field_12','(402) 613-3978'),(10571,1095,'_field_2','allyson.grieser@gmail.com'),(10572,1095,'_field_3','Bethany Everts is one of the most selfless and inspiring people I know. I have known her for 10 years and throughout this time of knowing her I know that she is the type of person that wants to pursue great things in life and uses all of her skills to help for the greater good. As a young lady Bethany loves such things as basketball, volunteering at church activities, participating in cross country and track, being a member of the band, and helping others in her community by donating her time. Everything that Bethany does I believe she does with a passion and because she has a genuine love for it, thus having her as a G.O.L.D.  girl would mean that she would put her heart and soul into this organization. Bethany is a beautiful soul that I know would be an asset to this organization and would make a positive impact. Her loving demeanor and acceptance towards all makes her an outstanding person to be around and work with. As a community member she is the cream of the crop and does whatever she can to help this community thrive. I am 100% certain that she would make a positive impact as a GOLD member due to her passion, drive, enthusiasm for doing all she can, her selflessness, and her bubbly personality that is infectious to all she meets. I strongly believe that this is a person that you need to be a GOLD girl. '),(10573,1095,'_field_17','Audrey West: (402)540-9938; awest0212@gmail.com \r\nKathy Ayars: (402)890-0069; kayars@lps.org'),(10574,1095,'_field_4','7'),(10575,1095,'_field_5',''),(10576,1095,'_sub_id','1095'),(10577,1096,'_form_id','1'),(10578,1096,'_seq_num','36'),(10579,1096,'_action','submit'),(10580,1096,'_field_1','Bethany Everts'),(10581,1096,'_field_6','East High School'),(10582,1096,'_field_7','Junior'),(10583,1096,'_field_8','Charlotte and Marcus Everts'),(10584,1096,'_field_9','3010 South 74th Street'),(10585,1096,'_field_10','(402) 613-5742'),(10586,1096,'_field_11','bethanyeverts@yahoo.com'),(10587,1096,'_field_13','(402) 613-9227'),(10588,1096,'_field_15','ceverts@lps.org'),(10589,1096,'_field_12','(402) 540-9938'),(10590,1096,'_field_2','awest0212@gmail.com'),(10591,1096,'_field_3','I think that Bethany will make a positive impact as a Lincoln G.O.L.D. member because I have been friends with her since we were in Kindergarten and thus have watched her grow up. I watched as she took the chance to volunteer at our church many times and consistently put her all into her work to make sure that the maximum amount of people are reached. She is compassionate to others when they need her help and personally takes it upon herself to make sure that not only are her friends happy but also that all those in her community are happy as well. She has taken the mediator position between our friends when they fight and continues to help dissolve the situation. She tries and succeeds in being her best self and she helps others be their best selves as well.'),(10592,1096,'_field_17','Allyson Grieser: 402-613-3988 allyson.grieser@gmail.com\r\nTara West: 402-499-1399 west.tara@hotmail.com'),(10593,1096,'_field_4','7'),(10594,1096,'_field_5',''),(10595,1096,'_sub_id','1096'),(10596,1097,'_form_id','1'),(10597,1097,'_seq_num','37'),(10598,1097,'_action','submit'),(10599,1097,'_field_1','Camden Hanel'),(10600,1097,'_field_6','Lincoln East'),(10601,1097,'_field_7','Junior'),(10602,1097,'_field_8','Greg and Tammy Hanel'),(10603,1097,'_field_9','7200 Old Post Rd.\r\nUnit 5'),(10604,1097,'_field_10','(531) 207-5456'),(10605,1097,'_field_11','camdenhanel@g